OHIBC Pressures habitat layer preparation

Compiled on Wed Jan 27 11:01:42 2016 by ohara

Assemble a habitat map for OHIBC pressures calculations.

Projection: BC Albers

Raster: * 500 m if reasonably fast - resolve 1 km features (e.g. intertidal buffer) * 1 km default/lowest res

Depth cutoffs: data layer for 0/50/200/200+ cutoffs available from BCMCA_ECO_Physical. Find other bathymetry layers for 60 m and 2000 m

use BCMCA processing script to find data locations by layer name

Define shelf/slope/deep not by 60m/200m/2000m but by:

  • “deep” is bottom of continental slope - outline defined by Pacific Offshore region
  • “shelf” is top of continental slope - all less than 200 m, outside of PO region
  • “slope” is region between shelf and slope
  • how should areas within PO region that are less than 2000 m be considered?
    • consider by depth - shallower than 2000 m = “slope”
    • shallower than 1000 m = “seamount”?
    • consider by topo - slope, ridge, depression = “slope”
